extract: Healdsburg is a city located in Sonoma County, in the North Bay region of California, United States. Situated along the Russian River, it lies at the convergence of three major wine-producing regions: the Alexander Valley, Dry Creek Valley, and Russian River Valley. As of the 2020 United States census, the population was 11,340. The city was incorporated in 1867 following waves of settlement during the California Gold Rush and expansion of the railroad. Healdsburg is part of the San Francisco Bay Area and contributes to the broader California wine industry.
